D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESens.%20Jeff%20Merkley%2C%20Josh%20Hawley%2C%20and%20Jon%20Ossoff%20came%20together%20with%20a%20new%20plan%20to%20ban%20lawmakers%20from%20trading%20stocks.%3Cp%3EBonnie%20Cash%2FAP%20Images%3B%20Tom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20group%20of%20senators%20came%20together%20around%20a%20new%20bill%20to%20ban%20lawmakers%20from%20trading%20stocks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20the%20most%20significant%20development%20on%20the%20issue%20in%20years%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20if%20it%20will%20get%20a%20vote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20what's%20in%20the%20new%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20a%20key%20Senate%20panel%20approved%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20ban%20lawmakers%20from%20trading%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Senate%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Government%20Affairs%20Committee%20approved%20the%20legislation%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20the%20E%3Cem%3Ending%20Trading%20and%20Holdings%20in%20Congressional%20Stocks%20(ETHICS)%20Act%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20by%20an%208-4%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20Sens.%20Rand%20Paul%20of%20Kentucky%2C%20Ron%20Johnson%20of%20Wisconsin%2C%20Mitt%20Romney%20of%20Utah%2C%20and%20James%20Lankford%20of%20Oklahoma%20voted%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20public%20doesn't%20think%20we%20should%20profit%20from%20having%20information%20that%20they%20don't%20have%2C%20and%20we%20shouldn't%26quot%3B%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Jeff%20Merkley%20of%20Oregon%2C%20one%20of%20the%20key%20sponsors%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20his%20office%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolling%20has%20shown%20for%20years%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20banning%20lawmakers%20from%20trading%20stocks%20in%20broadly%20popular%20among%20members%20of%20both%20parties.%20Several%20lawmakers%20have%20even%20campaigned%20on%20the%20issue.%20Yet%20a%20vote%20on%20legislation%20to%20address%20the%20public's%20concerns%20has%20remained%20elusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20Senate%20committee%20vote%20is%20the%20most%20significant%20progress%20on%20the%20effort%20in%20years.%20Here's%20what%20you%20should%20know%20about%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22279fe08d-6f4d-4a11-9dd5-855290fe6783%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20a%20sweeping%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20wouldn't%20take%20full%20effect%20until%202027%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20this%20bill%2C%20members%20of%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20President%20and%20Vice%20President%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20banned%20from%20purchasing%20stocks%20and%20cryptocurrencies%20beginning%2090%20days%20after%20the%20bill's%20signed%20into%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20on%20March%2031%2C%202027%20%E2%80%94%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20from%20now%20%E2%80%94%20a%20more%20complete%20ban%20takes%20place.%20Those%20same%20politicians%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20spouses%20and%20any%20dependent%20children%2C%20would%20have%20to%20sell%20off%20all%20of%20their%20stocks%20within%20120%20days%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20that%20delay%20is%20to%20give%20lawmakers%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20have%20large%20stock%20portfolios%20and%20may%20not%20have%20contemplated%20a%20trading%20ban%20when%20they%20were%20running%20for%20office%2C%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20rules.%20The%20bill%20also%20forbids%20lawmakers%20from%20buying%20stocks%20until%2090%20days%20after%20they've%20left%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20also%20comes%20with%20steep%20fines%20for%20politicians%20who%20break%20the%20law%3A%20Either%20one%20month's%20salary%20or%2010%25%20of%20the%20value%20of%20each%20stock%2C%20whichever%20is%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20bill%20would%20create%20a%20searchable%20database%20of%20lawmakers'%20financial%20holdings%20more%20broadly%2C%20which%20are%20currently%20only%20accessible%20via%20individual%20online%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20the%20legislation%20can%20be%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24989856%2Flew24315.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6fab198-4aaf-4e97-ba55-ee71a5676485%5C%22%3ELawmakers%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20blind%20trusts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20difference%20between%20this%20bill%20and%20previous%20proposals%20is%20that%20it%20doesn't%20allow%20for%20lawmakers%20to%20continue%20holding%20stocks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftom-malinowski-puts-stock-trades-blind-trust-congress-finances-transparency-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evia%20%26quot%3Bblind%20trusts%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20some%20have%20criticized%20as%20insufficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20sense%20that%20they're%20not%20really%20blind%2C%26quot%3B%20Merkley%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20easier%20and%20more%20straightforward%20to%20say%3A%20If%20you%20want%20to%20serve%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20serve%20the%20people%2C%20not%20your%20portfolio.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20still%20certain%20assets%20that%20lawmakers%20and%20their%20families%20could%20continue%20to%20hold%2C%20such%20as%20mutual%20funds%2C%20US%20Treasury%20bills%2C%20and%20municipal%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22500fe928-3edd-4374-9ff6-fd4337f1eedd%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20the%20most%20significant%20progress%20on%20a%20stock%20trading%20ban%20in%20years%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20either%20chamber%20got%20close%20to%20passing%20a%20stock%20trading%20ban%20was%20in%20September%202022%2C%20when%20House%20Democrats%20proposed%20a%20sweeping%20bill%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnancy-pelosi-stock-trading-ban-blind-trust-loophole-ethics-experts-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluded%20a%20major%20loophole%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20had%20little%20time%20to%20be%20vetted%20by%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-stock-trade-ban-vote-before-midterms-bill-text-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultimately%20yanked%20after%20opposition%3C%2Fa%3E%20quickly%20bubbled%20up.%20Many%20saw%20the%20effort%20as%20a%20sham%20designed%20to%20appease%20those%20who%20had%20been%20pushing%20for%20a%20stock%20trading%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20since%2C%20Merkley%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Jon%20Ossoff%20of%20Georgia%20and%20Josh%20Hawley%20of%20Missouri%20%E2%80%94%20worked%20together%20to%20create%20a%20new%20bipartisan%20bill%20that%20fused%20elements%20of%20different%20pieces%20of%20legislation%20that%20they%20had%20proposed%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bill%20was%20also%20sponsored%20by%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Gary%20Peters%20of%20Michigan%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241e1295f-cd67-41c7-892e-1073fb9e20e5%5C%22%3EIt's%20unclear%20when%20the%20bill%20would%20get%20a%20vote%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20progress%20represented%20by%20Wednesday's%20committee%20vote%2C%20it's%20unclear%20when%20or%20if%20the%20bill%20will%20come%20up%20for%20a%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20session%20remain%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20this%20year%2C%20and%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20has%20historically%20been%20hesitant%20to%20bring%20up%20bills%20that%20don't%20already%20have%20enough%20votes%20to%20pass.%20It's%20unclear%20if%20that's%20the%20case%20with%20this%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerkley%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20bill's%20best%20shot%20would%20be%20to%20attach%20it%20to%20another%20must-pass%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20government%20funding%20legislation%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20form%20of%20an%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20warned%20that%20the%20path%20ahead%20would%20be%20difficult%2C%20given%20that%20individual%20senators%20can%20hold%20up%20legislation%20fairly%20easily%20in%20the%20upper%20chamber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20person%20out%20of%20100%20can%20stop%20us%20from%20getting%20a%20debate%20on%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Merkley%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20hoping%20we%20will%20have%20a%20bill%20where%20there's%20enough%20momentum%20for%20critical%20amendments%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20that%20I%20can%20force%20a%20vote%20on%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-new-ban-stock-trading-merkley-ossoff-hawley-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721839419000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a034c62d66759f66fd986f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-new-ban-stock-trading-merkley-ossoff-hawley-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20key%20Senate%20committee%20marked%20up%20new%20legislation%20that%20would%20ban%20lawmakers%20from%20trading%20stocks.%20Now%20comes%20the%20hard%20part%3A%20Putting%20it%20up%20for%20a%20vote.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-new-ban-stock-trading-merkley-ossoff-hawley-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20bullish%20signals%20are%20pointing%20to%20more%20stock%20gains%20ahead%2C%20according%20to%20Bank%20of%20America%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22nyse%20trader%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F51ccafe0ecad04aa6900001d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20stock%20market%20rally%20is%20likely%20to%20c