2C%20CrowdStrike%2C%20is%20explaining%20exactly%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crowdstrike.com%2Ffalcon-content-update-remediation-and-guidance-hub%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20memo%20released%20Wednesday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CrowdStrike%20said%20that%20an%20update%20to%20its%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bdesigned%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20changing%20threat%20landscape%20at%20operational%20speed%26quot%3B%20contained%20an%20%26quot%3Bundetected%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20error%20%E2%80%94%20explained%20further%20in%20CrowdStrike's%20full%20memo%20included%20below%20%E2%80%94%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrowdstrike-global-it-outage-one-defective-it-update-sparked-chaos-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emass%20chaos%20around%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-american-warn-pilots-of-communication-issues-amid-grounding-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThousands%20of%20flights%20were%20cancelled%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmass-it-outage-911-lines-down-parts-of-us-havoc-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20911%20services%20went%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupermarkets-fast-food-chains-retailers-disrupted-global-it-outage-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretailers%20closed%20stores%20or%20only%20accepted%20cash%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmass-it-outage-companies-operations-airlines-affected-microsoft-crowdstrike-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehospital%20operations%20were%20delayed%20or%20disrupted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrowdStrike%20quickly%20deployed%20a%20fix%20to%20the%20issue%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrowdstrike-outage-why-taking-time-companies-recover-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20took%20time%20to%20go%20into%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20some%20systems%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffix-windows-computer-blue-screen-death-what-to-try-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequiring%20a%20manual%20reboot%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20amounted%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglobal-it-outage-y2k-24-years-later-crowdstrike-cyber-expert-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20IT%20outage%20in%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20companies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-flight-cancellations-delays-worst-hit-airline-it-outage-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20still%20recovering%20from%20the%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20CrowdStrike's%20memo%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreliminary%20Post%20Incident%20Review%20(PIR)%3A%20Content%20Configuration%20Update%20Impacting%20the%20Falcon%20Sensor%20and%20the%20Windows%20Operating%20System%20(BSOD)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThis%20is%20CrowdStrike's%20preliminary%20Post%20Incident%20Review%20(PIR).%20We%20will%20be%20detailing%20our%20full%20investigation%20in%20the%20forthcoming%20Root%20Cause%20Analysis%20that%20will%20be%20released%20publicly.%20Throughout%20this%20PIR%2C%20we%20have%20used%20generalized%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20Falcon%20platform%20for%20improved%20readability.%20Terminology%20in%20other%20documentation%20may%20be%20more%20specific%20and%20technical.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EWhat%20Happened%3F%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20July%2019%2C%202024%20at%2004%3A09%20UTC%2C%20as%20part%20of%20regular%20operations%2C%20CrowdStrike%20released%20a%20content%20configuration%20update%20for%20the%20Windows%20sensor%20to%20gather%20telemetry%20on%20possible%20novel%20threat%20techniques.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThese%20updates%20are%20a%20regular%20part%20of%20the%20dynamic%20protection%20mechanisms%20of%20the%20Falcon%20platform.%20The%20problematic%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20configuration%20update%20resulted%20in%20a%20Windows%20system%20crash.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ESystems%20in%20scope%20include%20Windows%20hosts%20running%20sensor%20version%207.11%20and%20above%20that%20were%20online%20between%20Friday%2C%20July%2019%2C%202024%2004%3A09%20UTC%20and%20Friday%2C%20July%2019%2C%202024%2005%3A27%20UTC%20and%20received%20the%20update.%20Mac%20and%20Linux%20hosts%20were%20not%20impacted.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20defect%20in%20the%20content%20update%20was%20reverted%20on%20Friday%2C%20July%2019%2C%202024%20at%2005%3A27%20UTC.%20Systems%20coming%20online%20after%20this%20time%2C%20or%20that%20did%20not%20connect%20during%20the%20window%2C%20were%20not%20impacted.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EWhat%20Went%20Wrong%20and%20Why%3F%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3ECrowdStrike%20delivers%20security%20content%20configuration%20updates%20to%20our%20sensors%20in%20two%20ways%3A%20%3Cem%3ESensor%20Content%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20is%20shipped%20with%20our%20sensor%20directly%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20is%20designed%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20changing%20threat%20landscape%20at%20operational%20speed.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20issue%20on%20Friday%20involved%20a%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20update%20with%20an%20undetected%20error.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ESensor%20Content%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ESensor%20Content%20provides%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20capabilities%20to%20assist%20in%20adversary%20response.%20It%20is%20always%20part%20of%20a%20sensor%20release%20and%20not%20dynamically%20updated%20from%20the%20cloud.%20Sensor%20Content%20includes%20on-sensor%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning%20models%2C%20and%20comprises%20code%20written%20expressly%20to%20deliver%20longer-term%2C%20reusable%20capabilities%20for%20CrowdStrike's%20threat%20detection%20engineers.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThese%20capabilities%20include%20Template%20Types%2C%20which%20have%20pre-defined%20fields%20for%20threat%20detection%20engineers%20to%20leverage%20in%20Rapid%20Response%20Content.%20Template%20Types%20are%20expressed%20in%20code.%20All%20Sensor%20Content%2C%20including%20Template%20Types%2C%20go%20through%20an%20extensive%20QA%20process%2C%20which%20includes%20automated%20testing%2C%20manual%20testing%2C%20validation%20and%20rollout%20steps.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20sensor%20release%20process%20begins%20with%20automated%20testing%2C%20both%20prior%20to%20and%20after%20merging%20into%20our%20code%20base.%20This%20includes%20unit%20testing%2C%20integration%20testing%2C%20performance%20testing%20and%20stress%20testing.%20This%20culminates%20in%20a%20staged%20sensor%20rollout%20process%20that%20starts%20with%20dogfooding%20internally%20at%20CrowdStrike%2C%20followed%20by%20early%20adopters.%20It%20is%20then%20made%20generally%20available%20to%20customers.%20Customers%20then%20have%20the%20option%20of%20selecting%20which%20parts%20of%20their%20fleet%20should%20install%20the%20latest%20sensor%20release%20('N')%2C%20or%20one%20version%20older%20('N-1')%20or%20two%20versions%20older%20('N-2')%20through%20Sensor%20Update%20Policies.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20event%20of%20Friday%2C%20July%2019%2C%202024%20was%20not%20triggered%20by%20Sensor%20Content%2C%20which%20is%20only%20delivered%20with%20the%20release%20of%20an%20updated%20Falcon%20sensor.%20Customers%20have%20complete%20control%20over%20the%20deployment%20of%20the%20sensor%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20Sensor%20Content%20and%20Template%20Types.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20used%20to%20perform%20a%20variety%20of%20behavioral%20pattern-matching%20operations%20on%20the%20sensor%20using%20a%20highly%20optimized%20engine.%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20a%20representation%20of%20fields%20and%20values%2C%20with%20associated%20filtering.%20This%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20stored%20in%20a%20proprietary%20binary%20file%20that%20contains%20configuration%20data.%20It%20is%20not%20code%20or%20a%20kernel%20driver.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20delivered%20as%20%26quot%3BTemplate%20Instances%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20are%20instantiations%20of%20a%20given%20Template%20Type.%20Each%20Template%20Instance%20maps%20to%20specific%20behaviors%20for%20the%20sensor%20to%20observe%2C%20detect%20or%20prevent.%20Template%20Instances%20have%20a%20set%20of%20fields%20that%20can%20be%20configured%20to%20match%20the%20desired%20behavior.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Template%20Types%20represent%20a%20sensor%20capability%20that%20enables%20new%20telemetry%20and%20detection%2C%20and%20their%20runtime%20behavior%20is%20configured%20dynamically%20by%20the%20Template%20Instance%20(i.e.%2C%20Rapid%20Response%20Content).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20provides%20visibility%20and%20detections%20on%20the%20sensor%20without%20requiring%20sensor%20code%20changes.%20This%20capability%20is%20used%20by%20threat%20detection%20engineers%20to%20gather%20telemetry%2C%20identify%20indicators%20of%20adversary%20behavior%20and%20perform%20detections%20and%20preventions.%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20behavioral%20heuristics%2C%20separate%20and%20distinct%20from%20CrowdStrike's%20on-sensor%20AI%20prevention%20and%20detection%20capabilities.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20Testing%20and%20Deployment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20is%20delivered%20as%20content%20configuration%20updates%20to%20the%20Falcon%20sensor.%20There%20are%20three%20primary%20systems%3A%20the%20Content%20Configuration%20System%2C%20the%20Content%20Interpreter%20and%20the%20Sensor%20Detection%20Engine.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20Content%20Configuration%20System%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Falcon%20platform%20in%20the%20cloud%2C%20while%20the%20Content%20Interpreter%20and%20Sensor%20Detection%20Engine%20are%20components%20of%20the%20Falcon%20sensor.%20The%20Content%20Configuration%20System%20is%20used%20to%20create%20Template%20Instances%2C%20which%20are%20validated%20and%20deployed%20to%20the%20sensor%20through%20a%20mechanism%20called%20Channel%20Files.%20The%20sensor%20stores%20and%20updates%20its%20content%20configuration%20data%20through%20Channel%20Files%2C%20which%20are%20written%20to%20disk%20on%20the%20host.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20Content%20Interpreter%20on%20the%20sensor%20reads%20the%20Channel%20File%20and%20interprets%20the%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%2C%20enabling%20the%20Sensor%20Detection%20Engine%20to%20observe%2C%20detect%20or%20prevent%20malicious%20activity%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20customer's%20policy%20configuration.%20The%20Content%20Interpreter%20is%20designed%20to%20gracefully%20handle%20exceptions%20from%20potentially%20problematic%20content.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ENewly%20released%20Template%20Types%20are%20stress%20tested%20across%20many%20aspects%2C%20such%20as%20resource%20utilization%2C%20system%20performance%20impact%20and%20event%20volume.%20For%20each%20Template%20Type%2C%20a%20specific%20Template%20Instance%20is%20used%20to%20stress%20test%20the%20Template%20Type%20by%20matching%20against%20any%20possible%20value%20of%20the%20associated%20data%20fields%20to%20identify%20adverse%20system%20interactions.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETemplate%20Instances%20are%20created%20and%20configured%20through%20the%20use%20of%20the%20Content%20Configuration%20System%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20Content%20Validator%20that%20performs%20validation%20checks%20on%20the%20content%20before%20it%20is%20published.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ETimeline%20of%20Events%3A%20Testing%20and%20Rollout%20of%20the%20InterProcessCommunication%20(IPC)%20Template%20Type%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ESensor%20Content%20Release%3A%20On%20February%2028%2C%202024%2C%20sensor%207.11%20was%20made%20generally%20available%20to%20customers%2C%20introducing%20a%20new%20IPC%20Template%20Type%20to%20detect%20novel%20attack%20techniques%20that%20abuse%20Named%20Pipes.%20This%20release%20followed%20all%20Sensor%20Content%20testing%20procedures%20outlined%20above%20in%20the%20Sensor%20Content%20section.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETemplate%20Type%20Stress%20Testing%3A%20On%20March%2005%2C%202024%2C%20a%20stress%20test%20of%20the%20IPC%20Template%20Type%20was%20executed%20in%20our%20staging%20environment%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20operating%20systems%20and%20workloads.%20The%20IPC%20Template%20Type%20passed%20the%20stress%20test%20and%20was%20validated%20for%20use.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETemplate%20Instance%20Release%20via%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crowdstrike.com%2Fblog%2Ffalcon-update-for-windows-hosts-technical-details%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannel%20File%20291%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20On%20March%2005%2C%202024%2C%20following%20the%20successful%20stress%20test%2C%20an%20IPC%20Template%20Instance%20was%20released%20to%20production%20as%20part%20of%20a%20content%20configuration%20update.%20Subsequently%2C%20three%20additional%20IPC%20Template%20Instances%20were%20deployed%20between%20April%208%2C%202024%20and%20April%2024%2C%202024.%20These%20Template%20Instances%20performed%20as%20expected%20in%20production.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EWhat%20Happened%20on%20July%2019%2C%202024%3F%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20July%2019%2C%202024%2C%20two%20additional%20IPC%20Template%20Instances%20were%20deployed.%20Due%20to%20a%20bug%20in%20the%20Content%20Validator%2C%20one%20of%20the%20two%20Template%20Instances%20passed%20validation%20despite%20containing%20problematic%20content%20data.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EBased%20on%20the%20testing%20performed%20before%20the%20initial%20deployment%20of%20the%20Template%20Type%20(on%20March%2005%2C%202024)%2C%20trust%20in%20the%20checks%20performed%20in%20the%20Content%20Validator%2C%20and%20previous%20successful%20IPC%20Template%20Instance%20deployments%2C%20these%20instances%20were%20deployed%20into%20production.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWhen%20received%20by%20the%20sensor%20and%20loaded%20into%20the%20Content%20Interpreter%2C%20problematic%20content%20in%20Channel%20File%20291%20resulted%20in%20an%20out-of-bounds%20memory%20read%20triggering%20an%20exception.%20This%20unexpected%20exception%20could%20not%20be%20gracefully%20handled%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20Windows%20operating%20system%20crash%20(BSOD).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EHow%20Do%20We%20Prevent%20This%20From%20Happening%20Again%3F%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3ESoftware%20Resiliency%20and%20Testing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Csection%3EImprove%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20testing%20by%20using%20testing%20types%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELocal%20developer%20testing%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EContent%20update%20and%20rollback%20testing%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStress%20testing%2C%20fuzzing%20and%20fault%20injection%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStability%20testing%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EContent%20interface%20testing%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdd%20additional%20validation%20checks%20to%20the%20Content%20Validator%20for%20Rapid%20Response%20Content.%20A%20new%20check%20is%20in%20process%20to%20guard%20against%20this%20type%20of%20problematic%20content%20from%20being%20deployed%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEnhance%20existing%20error%20handling%20in%20the%20Content%20Interpreter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3ERapid%20Response%20Content%20Deployment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EImplement%20a%20staggered%20deployment%20strategy%20for%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20in%20which%20updates%20are%20gradually%20deployed%20to%20larger%20portions%20of%20the%20sensor%20base%2C%20starting%20with%20a%20canary%20deployment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EImprove%20monitoring%20for%20both%20sensor%20and%20system%20performance%2C%20collecting%20feedback%20during%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20deployment%20to%20guide%20a%20phased%20rollout.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProvide%20customers%20with%20greater%20control%20over%20the%20delivery%20of%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20updates%20by%20allowing%20granular%20selection%20of%20when%20and%20where%20these%20updates%20are%20deployed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProvide%20content%20update%20details%20via%20release%20notes%2C%20which%20customers%20can%20subscribe%20to.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%20preliminary%20Post%20Incident%20Review%2C%20CrowdStrike%20is%20committed%20to%20publicly%20releasing%20the%20full%20Root%20Cause%20Analysis%20once%20the%20investigation%20is%20complete.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrowdstrike-memo-explains-faulty-update-it-outage-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721837336000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a12277fb2b6bedb05a0685%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrowdstrike-memo-explains-faulty-update-it-outage-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CrowdStrike%20reveals%20how%20a%20faulty%20Rapid%20Response%20Content%20update%20caused%20a%20global%20Microsoft%20IT%20outage%2C%20affecting%20airlines%2C%20banks%2C%20and%20retailers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ggoodwin%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Eliza%20Goodwin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrowdstrike-me