%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-war-machine-rebuilt-making-more-ammunition-nato-official-says-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwar%20machine%26quot%3B%20manufacturing%20has%20boomed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-worker-shortage-ukraine-war-military-wages-unemployment-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewages%20have%20jumped%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-companies-boom-lucrative-trade-deals-china-invasion-ukraine-putin-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20with%20alternative%20markets%20has%20strengthened%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20ministers%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20taking%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20signals%2C%20it%20becomes%20clear%20that%20everything%20is%20not%20as%20rosy%20with%20the%20Russian%20economy%20as%20Moscow%20would%20have%20us%20believe%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20group%2C%20which%20included%20representatives%20from%20countries%20such%20as%20Sweden%2C%20Poland%2C%20and%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Russia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-world-bank-upgrade-high-income-country-war-sanctions-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpanding%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20give%20off%20the%20illusion%20of%20stability%2C%20the%20authors%20asserted%20that%20its%20underlying%20source%20of%20growth%20is%20by%20no%20means%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20financial%20stimulus%20is%20the%20chief%20tailwind%20keeping%20Russia%20resistant%2C%20but%20the%20ministers%20noted%20that%20isn't%20an%20endless%20pillar%20of%20support.%20Two%20years%20into%20Moscow's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20government%20has%20nearly%20halved%20the%20liquid%20assets%20in%20Russia's%20national%20wealth%20fund%2C%20they%20wrote%20in%20one%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20also%20cited%20extreme%20interventions%20to%20question%20Russia's%20stability%2C%20including%20export%20bans%20and%20strict%20capital%20controls.%20These%20policies%2C%20coupled%20with%20hefty%20investment%20in%20Russia's%20wartime%20industry%2C%20indicate%20that%20Moscow%20is%20slipping%20back%20into%20a%20Soviet%20Union%20economy%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20could%20be%20perceived%20and%20mistaken%20as%20a%20'boost'%20to%20Russian%20growth%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20re-Sovietisation%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BHistory%20clearly%20shows%20that%20this%20is%20not%20a%20successful%20long-term%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20citing%20that%20private%20sector%20overheating%20will%20likely%20result%20in%20stagnation%20and%20boost%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eight%20ministers%20argued%20that%20these%20conditions%20make%20Western%20sanctions%20more%20important%20than%20ever%2C%20adding%20that%20pressure%20should%20be%20cranked%20up%20on%20Russia.%20They%20called%20for%20tighter%20restrictions%20on%20Moscow's%20energy%2C%20finance%2C%20and%20technology%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20maintain%20pressure%20on%20Moscow%2C%20the%20country's%20continued%20need%20for%20stimulus%20will%20force%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20turn%20toward%20monetary%20financing.%20According%20to%20the%20ministers%2C%20this%20will%20erode%20Russian%20cash%20reserves%20and%20add%20inflationary%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20noted%20that%20if%20the%20West%20is%20patient%20enough%2C%20Russia's%20confidence%20will%20eventually%20slump%20as%20long-term%20damage%20takes%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20should%20pressure%20be%20amplified%20on%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20but%20Western%20leaders%20should%20take%20a%20tougher%20stance%20on%20countries%20that%20provide%20Russia%20with%20needed%20goods%20for%20its%20war%2C%20the%20ministers%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20border%20and%20source%20count