ontent%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBihar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20epicentres%20of%20several%20paper%20leaks%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20NEET-UG%20test%2C%20has%20passed%20a%20stringent%20bill%20to%20curb%20malpractices%20in%20government%20exams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bihar%20Public%20Examinations%20(PE)%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Bill%2C%202024%2C%20was%20tabled%20by%20state%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Vijay%20Kumar%20Chaudhary%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20passed%20with%20a%20voice%20vote%20amid%20a%20walkout%20by%20the%20opposition.%20The%20walkout%20was%20to%20protest%20lawlessness%20and%20the%20denial%20of%20special%20status%20to%20Bihar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20which%20had%20first%20been%20introduced%20in%20the%20monsoon%20session%2C%20has%20strict%20provisions%2C%20including%20a%20prison%20term%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20those%20found%20guilty%20of%20involvement%20in%20irregularities%20in%20exams%20for%20both%20individuals%20and%20organisations.%20It%20also%20has%20a%20clause%20for%20attaching%20the%20properties%20of%20those%20found%20guilty%20and%20makes%20it%20difficult%20for%20people%20arrested%20for%20exam%20irregularities%20to%20get%20bail.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20passing%20its%20order%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20which%20it%20said%20there%20would%20be%20no%20retest%20for%20NEET-UG%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20had%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20paper%20for%20the%20exam%20had%20been%20leaked%20for%20at%20least%20two%20centres%2C%20in%20Bihar's%20Patna%20and%20Hazaribagh%20in%20Jharkhand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBihar%20has%20seen%20several%20paper%20leaks%20for%20state-level%20tests%20and%20gangs%20from%20the%20state%20have%20also%20been%20found%20involved%20in%20leaking%20papers%20or%20tampering%20with%20the%20examination%20process%20for%20national%20entrance%20exams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state's%20paper%20leak%20bill%20follows%20the%20notification%20of%20a%20central%20law%20last%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Public%20Examinations%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Act%2C%202024%2C%20which%20was%20notified%20on%20June%2021%2C%20any%20person%20or%20persons%20found%20guilty%20of%20leaking%20a%20paper%20or%20tampering%20with%20answer%20sheets%20will%20receive%20a%20minimum%20jail%20term%20of%20three%20years.%20This%20can%20be%20extended%20to%20five%20years%20with%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20All%20offences%20under%20the%20Act%20will%20be%20cognisable%20and%20non-bailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExamination%20service%20providers%20who%20have%20knowledge%20about%20a%20possible%20offence%20but%20do%20not%20report%20it%20can%20be%20fined%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20investigation%2C%20if%20it%20is%20established%20that%20any%20senior%20official%20from%20the%20service%20provider%20had%20allowed%20or%20was%20involved%20in%20committing%20the%20offence%2C%20he%20will%20face%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%20three%20years%2C%20which%20can%20go%20up%20to%2010%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%201%20crore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20examination%20authority%20or%20the%20service%20provider%20commits%20an%20organised%20crime%2C%20the%20jail%20term%20will%20be%20a%20minimum%20of%20five%20years%20and%20a%20maximum%20of%2010%2C%20and%20the%20fine%20will%20remain%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%2024%20lakh%20students%20had%20appeared%20for%20the%20NEET-UG%202024%20for%20undergraduate%20medical%20courses%2C%20which%20is%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Testing%20Agency%20(NTA)%2C%20on%20May%205.%20The%20results%20were%20announced%20on%20June%204%2C%2010%20days%20before%20schedule%2C%20but%20allegations%20of%20question%20paper%20leaks%20and%20grace%20marks%20to%20over%201%2C500%20students%20triggered%20protests.%20Cases%20were%20also%20filed%20in%20courts%2C%20including%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721816880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2015-08%2Fbihar-assembly-650_650x400_51438585587.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F10-year-jail-1-crore-fine-bihar-passes-bill-to-curb-paper-leaks-6178047%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bihar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20epicentres%20of%20several%20paper%20leaks%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20NEET-UG%20test%2C%20has%20passed%20a%20stringent%20bill%20to%20curb%20malpractices%20in%20government%20exams.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F10-year-jail-1-crore-fine-bihar-passes-bill-to-curb-paper-leaks-6178047%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F10-year-jail-1-crore-fine-bihar-passes-bill-to-curb-paper-leaks-6178047%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F10-year-jail-1-crore-fine-bihar-passes-bill-to-curb-paper-leaks-6178047%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Thane%20Woman%20Forged%20Docs%20To%20Meet%20Pak%20Man%20She%20%26quot%3BMarried%20Online%26quot%3B%2C%20Claim%20Cops%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20from%20Thane%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20who%20recently%20returned%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20is%20under%20police%20investigation.%20Authorities%20allege%20that%20she%20may%20have%20used%20false%20documents%2C%20including%20a%20forged%20name%20and%20Aadhaar%20card%2C%20to%20obtain%20a%20Pakistani%20visa%20to%20meet%20a%20man%20she%20married%20%26quot%3Bonline%26quot%3B%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20of%20Nagma's%20return%20from%20Pakistan%20came%20to%20the%20police's%20attention%20after%20came%20home%20on%20July%2017%20but%20on%20her%20documents%2C%20Nagma%20Noor%20Maksood%20Ali%20was%20Sanam%20Khan%20Rukh%2C%20the%20cops%20claimed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Nagma%2FSanam%20connected%20with%20Babar%20Bas