she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReva%E2%80%99s%20solar%20cooker%20is%20about%202-feet%20in%20length%20and%20has%20three%20rectangular%20shaped%20containers%20to%20place%20various%20dishes%20like%20%3Cem%3Edaal%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Evegetables%2C%20and%20rice%20separately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20reduce%20the%20cooking%20time%2C%20I%20use%20%3Cem%3Echana%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20rajma%20soaked%20overnight.%20One%20of%20the%20cons%20of%20this%20system%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20make%20chapatis%20and%20add%20tadka%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Edaal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20started%20eating%20wheat%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%3Cem%3Edaliya%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Ebaati.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAlso%2C%20we%20roast%20and%20add%20cumin%20and%20coriander%20to%20make%20the%20lentil%20taste%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20simplified%20food%20choices%20for%20us%20now.%20The%20taste%20has%20now%20become%20secondary%20for%20us.%20However%2C%20we%20personally%20find%20the%20taste%20to%20be%20slightly%20better%20as%20the%20food%20is%20cooked%20slowly%20and%20the%20taste%20of%20the%20vegetable%20is%20retained%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20limitation%20of%20the%20set%20up%2C%20Reva%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20do%20most%20of%20the%20cooking%20in%20the%20solar%20cookers%2C%20we%20have%20also%20kept%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(stove)%20as%20a%20backup%20for%20cloudy%20and%20rainy%20days.%20We%20collect%20firewood%20from%20trees%20around%20our%20house%20and%20also%20use%20coconut%20shells%20and%20cow%20dung%20cakes%20as%20fuel.%20We%20use%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eonly%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20backup%20for%20cooking%20that%20they%20use%20during%20cloudy%20days%20and%20at%20night%20is%20their%20stored%20solar%20energy.%20Their%20house%20has%20a%20small%20850%20VA%20solar%20inverter%20that%20delivers%20enough%20charge%20for%20low-wattage%20electrical%20appliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20fondly%20talks%20about%20how%20she%20repurposed%20and%20converted%20an%20old%20box-type%20solar%20cooker%20into%20a%20food%20dehydrator.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20dehydrate%20and%20preserve%20excess%20fruits%20when%20they%20have%20a%20bounty.%20The%20contraption%20is%20also%20used%20for%20roasting%20grains%2C%20nuts%20and%20even%20drying%20homegrown%20turmeric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357270%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EReva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Reva%2C%20solar%20cooking%20is%20also%20cost-effective.%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20we%20would%20be%20getting%20the%20LPG%20cylinder%20refilled%20every%202-3%20months.%20It%20would%20cost%20Rs%201%2C200%20per%20refill.%20We%20invested%20Rs%2018%2C000%20for%20the%20solar%20cooker.%20This%20was%20a%20one-time%20investment%20as%20there%20is%20no%20other%20recurring%20expense%20and%20maintenance%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20households%20use%20LPG%20for%20cooking%20purposes%20and%20add%20to%20the%20emission%20burden.%20Reva%20urges%20people%20to%20harness%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F306168%2Findian-oil-indoor-solar-cooking-stove-surya-nutan-save-lpg-reduce-carbon-footprint%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20energy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20is%20abundantly%20available%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20people%20think%20solar%20cooking%20is%20not%20convenient.%20With%20our%20experience%20of%20completely%20switching%20to%20solar%20cooking%2C%20we%20find%20it%20more%20convenient%20and%20easier%20than%20an%20LPG%20stove.%20Secondly%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20guilt-free%20cooking.%20There%20is%20an%20immense%20satisfaction%20knowing%20our%20food%20is%20cooked%20in%20sunlight%20effortlessly.%20We%20are%20not%20exploiting%20our%20planet%E2%80%99s%20resources%20anymore%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Reva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20managed%20to%20close%20this%20energy%20loop%20for%20ourselves.%20If%20this%20becomes%20aspirational%20and%20households%20use%20sunlight%20as%20energy%20then%20collectively%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20mitigate%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20All%20of%20us%20can%20think%20of%20adopting%20solar%20cooking%20as%20our%20first%20step%20towards%20energy%20self-sufficiency%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESource%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Foil-gas%2Flpg-imports-surge-60-in-five-years%2Farticleshow%2F107732630.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELPG%20imports%20surge%2060%25%20in%20five%20years%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3EBy%20Sanjee